Sentencas: This study investigates the functionality of bi-layered electrolytes in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: High performance Bi-layered electrolytes via atomic layer deposition for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A thin yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) layer is expected to protect the underlying gadolinia doped ceria (GDC) electrolyte from being chemically reduced and significantly improve cell stability and durability.
Titulo: High performance Bi-layered electrolytes via atomic layer deposition for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Although a thinner YSZ layer is preferable to minimize ohmic loss, there are limitations as to how thin the YSZ film can be and still serves as a valid protection layer.
Titulo: High performance Bi-layered electrolytes via atomic layer deposition for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The limitation is partially attributed to the inter-diffusion and significant morphological changes during the high temperature sintering processes.
Titulo: High performance Bi-layered electrolytes via atomic layer deposition for solid oxide fuel cells
